	   <tr><td colspan=2>The other thing to consider is that once your wisdom goes over 200 (which for a druid should happen long before level 60), the mana gained from each point of wisdom above 200 is drastically reduced.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have heard that it has been calculated that one point of wis equals one point of mana for each point over 200.  If that's the case, the testament is only 11 mana better than a CGS.  And also keep in mind that as you level, the actual AC gained from putting on a 10 AC item is more than just 10.  Try it and see.  Sure, neither item is going to save your low hp hide by itself, but the CGS would probably help protect the few hp you have.  And again, the mana is only useful if you're working from a full clip of mana.  If you're at anything less than full, mana gear is worth nothing to you.  AC gear works no matter how low your hp or mana gets.<br><br>If weight is an issue, well, that's another thing.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
